<subSubSection pageId="77" pageNumber="78" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="77.[151,1437,259,1222]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Remarks</emphasis>
. In addition to 5 previously described species here transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Just, 2022" authorityName="Just" authorityYear="2022" box="[1043,1149,1016,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Synopiidae" genus="Minitiron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1043,1149,1016,1041]" italics="true" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Minitiron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1157,1262,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1157,1262,1015,1041]" pageId="77" pageNumber="78" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, specimens belonging to this shallow water genus have been collected in numerous places in 
<collectingCountry box="[1017,1124,1051,1077]" name="Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
: from NE 
<collectingRegion box="[1236,1368,1051,1077]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Queensland</collectingRegion>
along the east, south, and west coasts north to around Dampier, 
<collectingRegion box="[796,999,1087,1114]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
; from 
<collectingRegion box="[1070,1179,1087,1113]" country="New Zealand" name="Auckland" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Auckland</collectingRegion>
Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1432,1087,1114]" name="New Zealand" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, and from several locations in 
<collectingCountry box="[481,584,1123,1149]" name="Thailand" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. A separate study of this apparently quite diverse group is needed. Therefore only one species from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[492,595,1159,1185]" name="Australia" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Australia</collectingCountry>
is being described here. Collection locations in Australian for material not reported here are shown in 
<figureCitation box="[457,539,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURE 47" captionStartId="85.[151,250,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[365,1227,186,1862]" captionTargetId="figure-15@85.[346,1241,181,1880]" captionTargetPageId="85" captionText="FIGURE 47. Distribution of Glandulotiron and Minitiron (Tironinae, Synopiidae) in Australia. A, Adelaide; B, Brisbane; D, Darwin, Da, Dampier; JB, Jervis Bay; L, Lizard Is.; M, Melbourne; Or.Is., Orpheus Island (type locality of Minitiron); P, Perth; PH, Port Hedland; S, Sydney; SB, Shark Bay; T, Townsville. Dots may represent more than one sample. Open circles: undescribed material of Minitiron." pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
